Integrated mean squared error

Let \(IMSE =\) integrated mean squared error. If \(C(h)\) is the true covariance function and \(\widehat{C}(h)\) is the estimate, then

\[ IMSE = \int_0^\infty \Big(C(h) - \widehat{C}(h)\Big)^2 \; dh. \]

\(C(h)\) and \(\widehat{C}(h)\) are evaluated on a grid from \(h = 0\) to 5, and the IMSE is estimated by the trapezoidal rule

\[ \widehat{IMSE} = \sum_{i=1}^N \frac{\big(C(h_{i-1}) - \widehat{C}(h_{i-1})\big)^2 + \big(C(h_i) - \widehat{C}(h_i)\big)^2}{2} \Big(\big(C(h_i) - \widehat{C}(h_i)\big)^2 - \big(C(h_{i-1}) - \widehat{C}(h_{i-1})\big)^2\Big). \]
